SHELL (
Figs 8
, 57; 
Tables 3–4
). Depressed conical, with 5.5–5.75 hardly convex whorls; protoconch almost smooth; teleoconch with irregular wrinkles; without distinct incised spiral lines; longish scales all over teleoconch; tuberculate around umbilicus; brownish-corneous; body whorl sharply keeled; aperture rounded rhombic; upper insertion of peristome descending; peristome expanded, reflexed and thickened; umbilicus slightly eccentric, very wide, comprising 38–40% of shell diameter, hardly obscured by columellar edge.
